[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether the native-image JUnit includes reflection metadata for tests, but that could cause issues if the main method isn't properly set up. I could aim for a JDK class with a public static main method to avoid needing a reflection config. Like `javax.tools.ToolProvider` lacks a main method, but what about `com.sun.tools.javac.Main`? I wonder if it’s the best choice. I might also consider targeting `org.codehaus.commons.compiler.samples.DemoBase`, which does have a main method. Reading through is essential!
